Likewise, also, in the case of contraries, for the definition of the contrary will be contrary according to one certain connexion of con­ traries,2 thus, if that is beneficial which is productive of good, what is productive of evil or is corruptive of good is injurious, since one of these must necessarily be contrary to that mention­ ed at first.
If then neither be contrary to that mentioned at first, it is clear that neither of the definitions afterwards given, can be the definition of the contrary, so that neither has the definition given at first been rightly given.
