THE elenchi, then, which belong to diction, are from these places, but the species of paralogism without diction are seven;
one from accident;
the second on account of what is asserted simply, or not simply, but in a certain respect, or some where, or at some time, or with a certain relation;
the third from ignorance of the elenchus;
the fourth from the consequent;
the fifth from petitio principii;
the sixth from placing non-causa pro causâ;
the seventh from making many interrogations, one.
