Those which belong to the consequent, are a part of accident, since what is consequent, hap­ pens ;
still it differs from accident in that it is only possible to assume accident in one thing, as that yellow and honey are the same, also whiteness and a swan, but what follows is always in many things, for those which are the same with one and the same thing, we consider the same with each other, wherefore there is an elenchus from the consequent.
Still this is not altogether true, as if it should be from accident,.
for snow, and swan, are the same, so far as each is white.
